reviewText: I really like the character of Maigret--he is so good at his detecting one murderafter another in a very low key manner but he never misses after much intriguedefinitely worth a purchase and also I love the on location in Paris or Belgiummaking it all the better--there are 2 Maigret one is subtitled which is this oneand the other actor playing Maigret is not sub-titled both are excellent in the part.
summary: An excellent story of one murder after another
Title: Maigret: Set 9

reviewText: Maigret: Set 9The problem with Mhz releases is the subtitles are large as far I can tell, and detracts from the viewing.Wish the subtitles could be resizeable if not removeable.Rather buy releases from other producers that don't have these negatives.7/6/2014Aspect is 1.73, quality of video is a bit grainy/hazy.
summary: non-removeable subtitles is a huge minus
Title: Maigret: Set 9

reviewText: For the real Maigret, I highly recommend the versions starring the actor Bruno Cremer. Outstanding casting and location work. This is also the most extensive series of the Simenon Maigret stories.
summary: The best Maigret version by far
Title: Maigret: Set 9

reviewText: We have all the Maigret series.  A MUST HAVE.., #9--- We love his subtle, soft spoken,and seemingly naive approach to solving a perplexing mystery. Sadly ,all great things come to an end and he is irreplaceable.  Since his passing(08/07/2010) we feel that in all probability a  #10 or beyond will not be forthcoming.  We re-watch and treasure the ones we have because there is always something new to find in the rewind..
summary: BRUNO CREMER--INTERNATIONAL FILM STAR--DOES IT AGAIN !!
Title: Maigret: Set 9

reviewText: Set nine includes the final six episodes of this outstanding series of Maigret mysteries.  Appropriately enough the last disc is set on Christmas eve and is an appropriate farewell.
Title: Maigret: Set 9

reviewText: Comparing this to the Gambon series, this series starring Cremer is a clear winner ... even with sub-titles. Let's face it they were written in French.
summary: Unfortunately, the last of the series
Title: Maigret: Set 9
